Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.60,0:00:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, class...\NTell me what the decision
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.54,0:00:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in the 1963 Stuttgart case\Nwas based upon.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.14,0:00:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, what is this silence...?\NIs this a Zen temple in the Orient?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.25,0:00:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Eimer... I would like to\Nhear your answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.75,0:00:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.76,0:00:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...uh... That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.86,0:00:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone! Is there anyone\Nwho will break this silence?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.44,0:01:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the chronic latecomer is here at last.\NYou're 13 minutes late...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.51,0:01:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Seems your part-time pizza delivery job\Nwas awfully busy today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.22,0:01:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry...Professor...Kronecker...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.62,0:01:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, then, let me ask you a question\Nbefore you sit down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.42,0:01:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have enough strength\Nto tell me what the basis was
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.03,0:01:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,for the decision in the Stuttgart case?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.90,0:01:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Uh...yes. Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.23,0:01:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The accused claimed that\Nthe kidnapping was a sham
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.04,0:01:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and that the victim's death\Nhad been due to an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.24,0:01:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,After an investigation\Nof the crime scene
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.84,0:01:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,it was found that the victim's death\Nhad indeed been accidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.41,0:01:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, based on the fact that the intent\Nto kill must be proven in a murder
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.45,0:01:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I believe that a sentence\Nof 15 years was handed down.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.16,0:01:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good.\NSit down, Nina Fortner.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.47,0:01:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.03,0:03:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You saved us, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.60,0:03:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If no one had been able to\Ngive him the answer,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.80,0:03:38.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Kronecker would have probably\Ndemanded 50-page reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.34,0:03:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,50 pages, if we were lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.44,0:03:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to treat Nina, to whom we're\Ngreatly indebted, to something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.74,0:03:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You can come, can't you Nina?\NJust the two of us...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.91,0:03:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Peter.\NI have a club meeting today.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.55,0:03:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,See you!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.05,0:03:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She turned you down again...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.25,0:03:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Peter, how many times was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.06,0:04:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Shut up! I'd like to see if there's anyone\Nwho can get Nina to agree to a date.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.00,0:04:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I give up...!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.48,0:04:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, no! If I'm late with my deliveries,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.98,0:04:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to get it\Nfrom the manager again!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.13,0:04:42.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home...!\NBoy, am I hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.40,0:04:44.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my, the neighbors\Ncan probably hear you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.73,0:04:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a young lady now.\NIt's not becoming.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.64,0:04:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Go and wash your hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.64,0:04:49.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, ma'am!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.01,0:04:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Mom, did you\Ncolor your hair?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.24,0:04:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks good, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.65,0:04:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly! You shouldn't be dying\Nyour hair so bright, at your age!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.92,0:05:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You're wrong, Dad.\NShe looks lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.99,0:05:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,She's not going to\Na masquerade party, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.35,0:05:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it be wonderful\Nfor Mom to be young forever?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.56,0:05:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.66,0:05:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes... Speaking of masquerades...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.00,0:05:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I saw some kids in costumes today.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.80,0:05:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes...\NIt's the St. Hadrian Costume Parade.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.50,0:05:26.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I had dressed up like that\Nwhen I was little. They were so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.11,0:05:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh...you did dress up\Nin a costume.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.81,0:05:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.52,0:05:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,O-Oh...that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.12,0:05:37.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.32,0:05:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see... It's around here...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.79,0:05:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, here it is!\NHere, look at this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.73,0:05:49.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.03,0:05:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You were so excited\Nand made such a fuss.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.34,0:05:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.50,0:05:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Oh, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.29,0:06:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,A costume parade...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.99,0:06:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Distant spring.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.26,0:06:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I forlornly wait for a spring\Nthat will never come... Hannah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.87,0:06:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Hannah... Will you hurry\Nand get over your broken heart?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.47,0:06:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.21,0:06:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me send you\Nthe world's most beautiful flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.01,0:06:39.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born to blanket you in flowers...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.78,0:06:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow... I wonder who sent this.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.79,0:06:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha...!\NI'm very impressed, Peter!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.43,0:06:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How have you been, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.20,0:06:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, well, I've been very well,\Nthankfully, Dr. Gaitel.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.93,0:06:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.50,0:07:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I could tell by the look\Non your face when you entered
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.17,0:07:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,this counseling room\Nthat your were doing well.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.57,0:07:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And do you no longer\Nhave that dream?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.38,0:07:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Of that monster appearing\Nout of the darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.48,0:07:16.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I've been sleeping so well,\NI have no time to dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.75,0:07:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder why I was plagued by\Nsuch a dream night after night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.69,0:07:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It's common for people to become\Ninsecure during their student years.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.36,0:07:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Dreams of the future become\Nconfused with other insecurities,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.16,0:07:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and you lose sight of who you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.37,0:07:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But what you are is something\Nyou can spend your whole life
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.17,0:07:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to learn, and never discover.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.81,0:07:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,All you can do now is be prepared\Nto spend your whole life searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.81,0:07:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and do only what you can do\Ntoward your future.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.91,0:07:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I will do my best.\NI want to become a public prosecutor.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.12,0:07:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's good. All right, I think we can\Nend our counseling session for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.02,0:07:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.46,0:08:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina Fortner... Such a cheerful girl...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.47,0:08:08.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can't help but feel\Nthat her cheerfulness
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.67,0:08:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,is a reaction to something\Nshe's running away from.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.77,0:08:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Some...vast...darkness...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.68,0:08:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't say that.\NDon't act so innocent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.25,0:08:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world\Nare you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.49,0:08:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born to\Nblanket you in flowers..."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.09,0:08:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I never thought you had\Nthe makings of a poet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.76,0:08:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know anything about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.46,0:08:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't be able to come up with words\Nlike those even if I stood on my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.60,0:08:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Then, who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.37,0:08:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I've given my email address\Nto only my friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.71,0:08:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.21,0:08:49.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn. All I know is that\NI have another rival in love!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.72,0:08:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Who in the world could it be...?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.82,0:09:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,This bizarre murder\Nthat took place in Munich...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.26,0:09:06.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The perpetrator,\Nafter shooting the parents to death,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.93,0:09:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,strangled the two children with a rope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.93,0:09:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'd like you to explain the ruling\Nof the judge from the court records...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.67,0:09:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina Fortner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.28,0:09:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.68,0:09:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you not understand the question?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.28,0:09:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,N-No...uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.88,0:09:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The trial was focused on\Nthe cold-blooded murder
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.75,0:09:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,of a whole family...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.29,0:09:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh...?\N– The evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.46,0:09:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,The evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.80,0:09:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh...? There are times\Nyou can't answer either, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.11,0:09:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.91,0:09:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Nina?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.31,0:09:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.82,0:10:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?\NYou want to go to the infirmary?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.52,0:10:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm all right.\NI just felt a little ill...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.32,0:10:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,After listening to the professor's story...\Nsuddenly...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.13,0:10:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? You mean that bizarre\Nmassacre of that family?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.50,0:10:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.10,0:10:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.34,0:10:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought you were awfully brave,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.54,0:10:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're more sensitive\Nthan I expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.21,0:10:28.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see a horror movie\Nthat terrified you as a child?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.51,0:10:32.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I know! I'll bet that counselor,\NDr. Gaitel, would probably say...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.75,0:10:34.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look back on\Nwhy this happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.75,0:10:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find it was nothing significant.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.65,0:10:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, why don't you think back\Non your childhood..."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.96,0:10:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.86,0:10:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.33,0:10:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember anything\Nbefore the age of ten...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.22,0:11:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,My memories...\NMy childhood memories...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.73,0:11:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.04,0:11:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.14,0:11:33.30,Default,,0,0,0,,They were a very nice couple...\NTo think they were killed like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.01,0:11:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Children?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.55,0:11:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, now that you mention it,\Nthey had a son.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.35,0:11:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,His name was Michael, I think.\NThey lived together about two years.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.95,0:11:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A boy? Was there a boy...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.86,0:11:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, there was.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.46,0:11:53.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't his name Michael?\NHe was around fourteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.06,0:11:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Michael, you say...?\NI seem to remember him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.97,0:12:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Why? Are you the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.30,0:12:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Michael Reichmann.\NHe was a student in my class.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.51,0:12:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But he didn't leave\Nmuch of an impression.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.41,0:12:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm embarrassed to say this,\Nbut I don't remember him well.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.48,0:12:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if he had any friends.\NAnd, there are no records...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.29,0:12:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything burned\Nin a fire six years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.20,0:12:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There definitely was a boy\Nnamed Michael living here{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.13,0:12:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}in Cologne until six years ago...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.14,0:12:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}And.. .Michael's real name...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.94,0:12:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Johan... I've used that name before...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.91,0:12:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who. .. are you...?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.82,0:12:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But what's the use in knowing that?\NWhat's the use?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.82,0:12:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}He is a serial-killer who is a twin...\NThat's all there is.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.76,0:13:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What am I doing...?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.87,0:13:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A twin! What about his sister?\NWhere did his twin sister go?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.57,0:13:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,"I will come for you soon..."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.41,0:13:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is this...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.71,0:13:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll come for me soon...?\NWhat does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.72,0:13:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A child...? Yes, there was...\Nabout 7 or 3 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.63,0:13:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So Mr. and Mrs. Heinemann,\Nwho were killed, were fostering a boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.53,0:13:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he like?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.23,0:13:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,What was he like...?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.20,0:13:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.24,0:13:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And he only lived with them\Nabout a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.14,0:13:49.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember\Nanything about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.85,0:13:52.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't that boy have a sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.55,0:13:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.15,0:13:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen, I just want to forget about\Nwhat happened to that couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.95,0:14:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I even thought about moving away\Nafter it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.80,0:14:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I know about that boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.00,0:14:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on in. I was just about to\Nfix some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.91,0:14:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.21,0:14:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...yes. Thank you.\NUh...I...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.42,0:14:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Have a seat.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.74,0:14:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Please have some tea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.68,0:15:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.99,0:15:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a doctor, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.86,0:15:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy told me.\NYou're Dr. Tenma, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.17,0:15:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He's coming for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.97,0:15:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.20,0:15:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I have no idea.\NIt was an anonymous message.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.71,0:15:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You look so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.58,0:15:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not thinking a prince\Non a white horse
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.01,0:15:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,will be coming for you, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.02,0:15:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you jealous?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.49,0:15:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go,\Ndaydreaming again, Nina.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.52,0:15:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"I was born to blanket you in flowers..."
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.03,0:15:46.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There aren't any kids\Nwho talk like that today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.73,0:15:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.33,0:15:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, listen. Haven't you noticed\Na strange boy in class recently?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.73,0:15:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh! Yes, I have!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.40,0:15:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The one who calmly sits in\Nthat "legendary seat" in Room 12,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.54,0:16:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,where you're bound to be called on\Nby the teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.54,0:16:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, he's never called on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.95,0:16:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. And do you know,\Nhe stares at Nina all through class!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.88,0:16:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\N– He's the one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.05,0:16:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.29,0:16:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You know...!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.59,0:16:13.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Your prince on the white horse!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.49,0:16:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy was extremely grateful\Nto you, Dr. Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.90,0:16:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He said you were the one\Nwho saved him;
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.90,0:16:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you meant more to him than a parent.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.60,0:16:30.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What name did he go by?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.87,0:16:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Franz... But he said\Nit wasn't his real name.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.21,0:16:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He trusted you enough\Nto tell you that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.39,0:16:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That Franz, who had shown up\Nout of the blue,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.42,0:16:50.09,Default,,0,0,0,,was cared for by\NMr. and Mrs. Heinemann,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.19,0:16:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,who lived in the flat across the hall,\Nfor a year.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.83,0:17:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,No, actually, it was 14 months\Nfrom March 1937 to April 1933.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.97,0:17:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, one day, he suddenly vanished.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.54,0:17:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He was very bright.\NAnd he was well-mannered.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.98,0:17:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Did he used to\Ncome to this apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.55,0:17:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Every day. I lived alone\Nso I always welcomed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.96,0:17:25.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He sat in that seat\Nand spent his time studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.86,0:17:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In no time, he had mastered
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.70,0:17:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the English and French\Nthat I taught him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.27,0:17:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,By the time he disappeared,\Nhe was fluent in both.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.41,0:17:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That 12-year-old boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.28,0:17:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there anything else\Nyou remember about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.51,0:17:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He always listened closely\Nto my stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.22,0:17:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,What stories do you think\Nhe was most interested in?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.32,0:17:54.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.72,0:17:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,War stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.83,0:17:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,War...?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.39,0:18:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,During World War II,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.96,0:18:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I was on the crew of a U-boat.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.77,0:18:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,His favorite story\Nwas about the time
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.27,0:18:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we were attacked by a destroyer\Nof the Allied Forces...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.87,0:18:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We were at a depth of 120 meters...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.08,0:18:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We were attacked by the enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.48,0:18:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and although we had suffered\Na fatal blow, we kept going.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.48,0:18:24.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Inside that groaning ship,\Nwe all waited in terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.29,0:18:30.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We returned from that living hell\N33 hours later.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.79,0:18:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,An ordinary child would probably
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.76,0:18:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,look at this as\Nanother adventure story...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.40,0:18:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But that boy was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.30,0:18:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What he was\Nmost interested in was...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.21,0:18:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.67,0:18:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Extreme terror.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.91,0:18:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What is the reaction of a person\Nstanding on the edge of death?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.91,0:18:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,That was his only interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.48,0:18:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He took pleasure in terror!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.46,0:19:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Wh-What sort of expression
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.76,0:19:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,did he have while\Nlistening to your stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.86,0:19:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably had a gleam in his eye,\Nand a smile on his face.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.07,0:19:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Probably?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.64,0:19:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I am blind, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.87,0:19:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I know neither his real name,\Nnor what he looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.88,0:19:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, you said that boy\Ntrusted me, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.69,0:19:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He never trusts anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.96,0:19:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's only one person\Nhe's ever trusted--his sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.00,0:19:42.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I-I'm looking for that sister!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.40,0:19:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,He said he would go and collect her\Nwhen she turned twenty.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.80,0:19:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.00,0:19:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,To Heidelberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.61,0:19:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.88,0:19:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Ride carefully on your scooter.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.01,0:19:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I will!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.32,0:20:01.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Bye, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.72,0:20:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.42,0:20:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Good bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.63,0:20:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it's time...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.13,0:20:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.20,0:20:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We decided, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.84,0:20:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That we'd tell her on her 20th birthday\Nthat she's not our child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.75,0:20:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait, I can't...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.75,0:20:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?\NYou wanted to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.22,0:20:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We told him you'd wait for him here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.46,0:20:47.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't screw up,\Nwith your "prince on a white horse."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.36,0:20:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,See you later!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.26,0:20:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... Ciara! Beata!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.27,0:20:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How could they do this\Nbehind my back...!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.51,0:21:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.71,0:21:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.29,0:21:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,H-How do you do...\NYou're Nina Fortner?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.13,0:21:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.03,0:21:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...I'm Otto Hubermann...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.40,0:21:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, hello...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.52,0:21:49.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who is he...?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.26,0:21:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who is he?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.16,0:21:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I've seen him... somewhere. ..before...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.31,0:22:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who are you...?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.39,0:22:26.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Huh...?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.53,0:22:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina!\N– Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.33,0:22:30.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina! What's wrong?\NAre you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.13,0:22:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina, wake up!\N– Nina! Nina!?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.83,0:22:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina, wake up!\N– Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.34,0:22:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Nina!\N– Hey, Nina!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.64,0:22:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Nina, are you all right?!
